{"word":"ἅμμα","slug":"ἅμμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἅμμα</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἅπτω'><el>ἅπτω</el></a>\n<p/><i>anything tied</i> or <i>made to tie</i>, and so,<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a knot</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a noose, halter</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a band</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἅ. παρθενίας</el> the maiden <i>girdle</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b>in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <i>the wrestler's arms</i> or <i>hug</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}